  "texts": [
    "ZigBee, in particular, is a versatile, integrated short-range wireless communication technology commonly used for implementing IoT in agriculture (Farooq et al. 2019).",
    "As illustrated in Table 2, IoT sensors are commonly used in agriculture to improve efficiency and sustainability.",
    "These sensors have a wide range of applications in the agricultural sector, including smart greenhouse systems, automation of farming machinery, animal tracking, plant disease and pest monitoring, grain storage monitoring, and data analysis (Cihan 2023).",
    "By integrating IoT sensors into agriculture, farmers can collect real-time data on weather conditions, soil moisture levels, plant diseases, and pests.",
    "This data empowers farmers to make informed decisions and optimize resource allocation, leading to improved farming operations (Cihan 2023)."
  ]
}